-- Total Petroleum Ghana's First Quarter Net Income Climbed 74% as Sales Rose
-- Emily Bowers
-- 2010-04-26T07:49:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/total-petroleum-ghana-s-first-quarter-net-income-climbed-74-as-sales-rose.html

          
          
             Total Petroleum Ghana Ltd., a unit
of Franceâ€™s Total SA, said first-quarter net income rose 74
percent as sales climbed.  
 Profit after tax for the three months through March rose to
4.2 million cedis, from 2.4 million cedis a year earlier, the
Accra-based company said in an advertisement published in the
Business and Financial Times newspaper today.  
 Sales rose to 177.8 million cedis from 99.2 million cedis a
year earlier, the company said.  
